   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support 80 abandoned children in Cape Town</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fikelela Childrens Centre is based in Khayelitsha - a township in Cape Town that has high numbers of orphans and abandoned children. One in three adults is HIV+, and the community has a high level of unemployment, crime and shack housing. Many struggle to get enough food.  We run a children&apos;s home to care for the children while we find a loving &apos;forever family&apos; in the community. We support the foster parents for as long is necessary - with food parcels, emotional support, and advice</narrative>
  </description>
